  "stagger_strategy": "Potato and Soybean areas are split into two batches (A and B), planted 7 sols apart. This produces offset harvests within each zone, ensuring continuous food availability rather than feast/famine cycles. Turnaround between harvest and replanting is 5 sols for bed preparation and replanting. Lettuce, Spinach, Radish, and Basil cycle fast enough that staggering is unnecessary -- their short turnaround provides near-continuous supply naturally.",
